    a: "No, and this is one of the most misunderstood points in specialty coffee. Hawaii grows coffee in many regions: Kona, Ka'u, Puna, Hamakua, Maui, Molokai, Kauai. A bag labeled 'Hawaiian coffee' might be from any of those origins or a blend. Only beans grown specifically on the Kona coast of the Big Island can be called Kona at all, and only bags labeled '100% Kona' are guaranteed to be all Kona. 'Hawaiian coffee' and 'Kona coffee' are not synonyms."
